In particular, Lyons examines the practices and philosophies of rural farmers who value the decomposing layers of leaves, which make the soils that sustain life in the Amazon, and shows how the study and stewardship of the soil point to alternative frameworks for living and dying. In outlining the life-making processes that compose and decompose into soil, Lyons theorizes how life can thrive in the face of the violence, criminalization, and poisoning produced by militarized, growth-oriented development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aEnvironmental degradationzColombiazPutumayo (Department) 0aEnvironmental degradationzColombiazPutumayo (Department). 0aNaturexEffect of human beings onzColombiazPutumayo (Department) 0aNaturexEffect of human beings onzColombiazPutumayo (Department). 0aSoil degradationzColombiazPutumayo (Department) 0aSoil degradationzColombiazPutumayo (Department). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478009207zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478009207423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478009207/original  a978-3-11-069631-8  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBO